A MURDER MESSAGE IN A BOTTLE
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    Anyone who has gone wandering up the River Crane in wellies knows
    that there is often more than hungry ducks and plastic bottles
    coming down on the tide. After centuries of carving its way
    through Tudor middens, Georgian gunpowder mills, Victorian rubbish
    dumps and wartime back gardens the Crane can offer many surprises
    to the keen-eyed mudlark. from porcelain pot tops and tin hats
    to cast iron pokers and earthenware bottles saying
    'Richmond Bottling'.

