NEW TRAIL TO BE LAID IN CRANE PARK ISLAND NATURE RESERVE
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    An enhanced, interactive nature trail will be laid on Crane Park
    Island Nature Reserve following a 4,228 pound grant from the
    Council's Community Fund.

    London Wildlife Trust is working to improve the island's nature
    trail by installing numbered oak posts which link to an information
    map. The posts will have interactive tactile panels which children
    can use to make rubbings from which will tell them about the
    history and wildlife of the area.

